2023-12-12, **Cosmological Constraints on Neutrino Mass within Consistent Cosmological Models**, Ye-Huang Pang et.al., [2312.07188v1](http://arxiv.org/abs/2312.07188v1)

 Recently, the emergence of cosmological tension has raised doubts about the consistency of the $\Lambda$CDM model. In order to constrain the neutrino mass within a consistent cosmological framework, we investigate three massive neutrinos with normal hierarchy (NH) and inverted hierarchy (IH) in both the axion-like EDE (Axi-EDE) model and the AdS-EDE model. We use the joint datasets including cosmic microwave background (CMB) power spectrum from Planck 2018, Pantheon of type Ia supernova, baryon acoustic oscillation (BAO) and $H\_0$ data from SH0ES. For the $
u$Axi-EDE model, we obtain $\sum m\_{
u,\mathrm{NH}} < 0.152$ eV and $\sum m\_{
u,\mathrm{IH}} < 0.178$ eV, while for the $
u$AdS-EDE model, we find $\sum m\_{
u,\mathrm{NH}} < 0.135$ eV and $\sum m\_{
u,\mathrm{IH}} < 0.167$ eV. Our results exhibit a preference for the normal hierarchy in both the $
u$Axi-EDE model and the $
u$AdS-EDE model.
